        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Request Deduplication"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Request deduplication (also called in-flight coalescing or request collapsing) is the pattern of detecting multiple identical in-flight LLM requests and routing them all to a single upstream call, then fanning the response out to all waiting callers. Unlike caching \u2014 which serves a stored response \u2014 deduplication acts while the original request is still in progress, so the first caller sets the latency floor and all subsequent identical requests pay no additional cost or latency premium."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How In-Flight Coalescing Works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "In-flight coalescing: Request A triggers an LLM call. Requests B and C arrive with the same cache key while A is still in progress; instead of launching new LLM calls, they subscribe to A's future. When the response arrives at t=800ms it is fanned out to all three callers. Result: 1 LLM call, 3 satisfied callers."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The mechanism uses a shared dict of in-flight futures, keyed by request fingerprint:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Request A arrives. No entry in the in-flight dict \u2192 create a Future, store it, start the LLM call."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Request B arrives with the same key. Entry exists \u2192 subscribe to A's Future and await it."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Request C arrives with the same key. Same \u2014 subscribe to A's Future."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "LLM call completes \u2192 resolve the Future with the response."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "All subscribers (A, B, C) receive the resolved value simultaneously."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The cost and GPU compute of one LLM call is amortised across all subscribers. For popular queries (FAQ, common classifications, shared prompts), the dedup ratio can be 10\u201350\u00d7 during traffic spikes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "asyncio-based in-process deduplication"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, hashlib, json\nfrom typing import Any\n\nclass RequestDeduplicator:\n    \"\"\"\n    Coalesces identical concurrent LLM requests into a single upstream call.\n    Thread-safe within a single asyncio event loop.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        # Maps fingerprint -> asyncio.Future holding the in-progress result\n        self._in_flight: dict[str, asyncio.Future] = {}\n        self._lock = asyncio.Lock()\n\n    def _fingerprint(self, model: str, messages: list[dict], temperature: float) -> str | None:\n        # Only deduplicate deterministic requests (temperature = 0)\n        if temperature != 0.0:\n            return None\n        payload = json.dumps(\n            {\"model\": model, \"messages\": messages, \"temperature\": temperature},\n            sort_keys=True,\n        )\n        return \"dedup:\" + hashlib.sha256(payload.encode()).hexdigest()\n\n    async def call(\n        self,\n        model: str,\n        messages: list[dict],\n        temperature: float,\n        llm_fn,          # async callable (model, messages, temperature) -> Any\n    ) -> Any:\n        key = self._fingerprint(model, messages, temperature)\n\n        if key is None:\n            # Stochastic request \u2014 no deduplication, call directly\n            return await llm_fn(model, messages, temperature)\n\n        async with self._lock:\n            if key in self._in_flight:\n                # Another caller is already running this request; subscribe\n                fut = self._in_flight[key]\n                subscriber = True\n            else:\n                # We are the first caller; register and start the LLM call\n                fut = asyncio.get_event_loop().create_future()\n                self._in_flight[key] = fut\n                subscriber = False\n\n        if subscriber:\n            # Wait for the in-flight request to complete\n            return await asyncio.shield(fut)\n\n        # We are the originator; run the LLM call and resolve the future\n        try:\n            result = await llm_fn(model, messages, temperature)\n            fut.set_result(result)\n            return result\n        except Exception as exc:\n            fut.set_exception(exc)\n            raise\n        finally:\n            async with self._lock:\n                self._in_flight.pop(key, None)\n\n\n# Singleton for the process\ndeduplicator = RequestDeduplicator()"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Usage in a FastAPI endpoint"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom openai import AsyncOpenAI\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\napp = FastAPI()\nclient = AsyncOpenAI()\n\nclass ChatRequest(BaseModel):\n    model: str = \"gpt-4o-mini\"\n    messages: list[dict]\n    temperature: float = 0.0\n\nasync def _llm_call(model: str, messages: list[dict], temperature: float) -> dict:\n    resp = await client.chat.completions.create(\n        model=model,\n        messages=messages,\n        temperature=temperature,\n    )\n    return {\n        \"content\": resp.choices[0].message.content,\n        \"model\": resp.model,\n        \"input_tokens\": resp.usage.prompt_tokens,\n        \"output_tokens\": resp.usage.completion_tokens,\n    }\n\n@app.post(\"/v1/chat\")\nasync def chat(req: ChatRequest) -> dict:\n    return await deduplicator.call(\n        model=req.model,\n        messages=req.messages,\n        temperature=req.temperature,\n        llm_fn=_llm_call,\n    )"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The originator and all subscribers receive exactly the same response object. If the LLM call raises an exception, the Future's exception is propagated to every subscriber \u2014 they all see the same error, which is the correct behaviour."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Distributed Deduplication with Redis"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In-process deduplication only works within a single server process. With multiple API server instances behind a load balancer, the same request can reach two different processes simultaneously and launch two LLM calls. A Redis-based distributed lock extends deduplication across the fleet:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, hashlib, json, time\nimport redis.asyncio as aioredis\n\nredis_client = aioredis.Redis(host=\"localhost\", port=6379)\nLOCK_TTL = 120   # seconds \u2014 must exceed max LLM generation time\n\nasync def distributed_dedup_call(\n    key: str,\n    llm_fn,\n    result_ttl: int = 60,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Distributed deduplication via Redis.\n\n    Strategy:\n    1. Try to SET the lock key with NX (only if not exists).\n    2. If we won the lock: run LLM, write result, release lock.\n    3. If we lost the lock: poll until the result key appears, then return it.\n    \"\"\"\n    lock_key = f\"dedup:lock:{key}\"\n    result_key = f\"dedup:result:{key}\"\n\n    # Check if a previous call already cached a result\n    existing = await redis_client.get(result_key)\n    if existing:\n        return json.loads(existing)\n\n    # Try to become the originator\n    won_lock = await redis_client.set(lock_key, \"1\", nx=True, ex=LOCK_TTL)\n\n    if won_lock:\n        # We are the originator\n        try:\n            result = await llm_fn()\n            serialised = json.dumps(result)\n            await redis_client.setex(result_key, result_ttl, serialised)\n            return result\n        finally:\n            await redis_client.delete(lock_key)\n    else:\n        # We are a subscriber \u2014 poll until the result appears\n        deadline = time.monotonic() + LOCK_TTL\n        while time.monotonic() < deadline:\n            await asyncio.sleep(0.1)\n            value = await redis_client.get(result_key)\n            if value:\n                return json.loads(value)\n        raise TimeoutError(f\"Dedup wait exceeded {LOCK_TTL}s for key {key}\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Polling vs. pub/sub notification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The polling loop above checks every 100ms. For low-latency applications, replace polling with a Redis pub/sub notification so subscribers wake the instant the result is written:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, json\nimport redis.asyncio as aioredis\n\npub_client = aioredis.Redis(host=\"localhost\", port=6379)\nsub_client = aioredis.Redis(host=\"localhost\", port=6379)\n\nasync def wait_for_result_pubsub(result_key: str, channel: str, timeout: float = 120.0) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Subscribe to a Redis channel; return when the result key is published.\"\"\"\n    pubsub = sub_client.pubsub()\n    await pubsub.subscribe(channel)\n    try:\n        # Check if already done (race: result written before subscribe)\n        existing = await pub_client.get(result_key)\n        if existing:\n            return json.loads(existing)\n\n        deadline = asyncio.get_event_loop().time() + timeout\n        async for message in pubsub.listen():\n            if message[\"type\"] == \"message\":\n                return json.loads(message[\"data\"])\n            if asyncio.get_event_loop().time() > deadline:\n                raise TimeoutError(\"Pubsub wait timed out\")\n    finally:\n        await pubsub.unsubscribe(channel)\n        await pubsub.close()\n\nasync def originator_publish(result_key: str, channel: str, result: dict, ttl: int = 60) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Write result and notify all subscribers.\"\"\"\n    serialised = json.dumps(result)\n    await pub_client.setex(result_key, ttl, serialised)\n    await pub_client.publish(channel, serialised)"
          }
        ]
      },
