      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Apply Request Deduplication"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "High-traffic classification endpoints: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The same document or label set is submitted by multiple pipeline workers simultaneously \u2014 dedup reduces N identical calls to 1."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Shared system prompts under concurrent load: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Multiple users ask the same FAQ question within the same 500ms window during a traffic spike \u2014 dedup coalesces the burst."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Client retry storms: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A slow response causes the client to retry before the original completes; idempotency-key dedup prevents paying twice for the same logical request."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Webhook fan-out: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A single incoming event triggers N subscribers that all call the LLM with the same context \u2014 dedup collapses them to 1 call."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deduplication is most valuable when the request rate for identical prompts exceeds the LLM's tokens-per-second throughput \u2014 i.e., when new duplicate requests arrive faster than the originator completes. At low traffic it adds complexity for little gain; the caching layer already handles repeated queries with a warm cache."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Request deduplication coalesces concurrent identical LLM requests into a single upstream call, fanning the response out to all subscribers when it resolves. In-process deduplication uses an asyncio Future dict keyed by request fingerprint (SHA-256 of model + messages, temperature=0 only); distributed deduplication uses a Redis NX lock plus result key with pub/sub notification for zero-poll wake-up. Unlike caching, dedup applies while the request is in-flight and has no TTL concern \u2014 the state is ephemeral and self-cleaning. The two patterns are complementary: deduplication handles burst spikes (identical requests in the same 500ms window); caching handles repeated queries across longer time horizons. Both should be instrumented with hit rate, subscriber wait time, and error fan-out metrics."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
